1. .upper() and .lower() string method

1. .upper() allow you to making everythings in UPPER Case.

Ex.
all_lower = "There are no capital letter here."

print(all_lower.upper())

OutPut:- THERE ARE NO CAPITAL LETTER here

all_upper = "THIS IS SHOUTING TEXT!!"

print(all_upper.lower)

OutPut:- this is shouting text


2. .isupper() and .islower() string method

.isupper() returns boolean value false
It only returns TRUE if the all letter in the string is UPPER CASE.

Ex. print("Mixed Case".isupper())
# OutPut:- False, 

print("ALL CAPS!".isupper())
# OutPut:- TRUE

.islower() return booleans value false 
It only return TRUE if the all letter in the string is lower case.

Ex. print("HELLO".islower())
# OutPut:- False

print("$100 is a lot to make in an hour.".islower())
# OutPut:- True

